product_name: FENTY BEAUTY by RihannaGrip Trip Hydrating + Plumping Primer
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeA gripping primer with hydrating + plumping skincare benefits that delivers a smooth, hydrated finish that makes your makeup last up to 12 hours + sweat & humidity. Maple Sap Extract locks in makeup, while Butterfly Lavender Extract hydrates. This silicone-free primer creates the perfect canvas.
details: DetailsBenefitsHydrates, smooths + plumps skinResists sweat + humidityNo flashbackKey IngredientsMaple Sap Extract extends makeup wear for up to 12 hoursButterfly Lavender Extract helps to hydrate and plump skinItem 2646009How To UseFor the ultimate smooth and hydrated effect, use fingers to press primer into the skin - a little goes a long way. Start at the center of the face and work your way out.IngredientsPurple Base Ingredients: Aqua/Water/Eau, Propanediol, Diglycerin, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Betaine, Diisostearyl Malate, Polyglycerin-3, Isopropyl Myristate, Tribehenin, Silica, Arachidyl Alcohol, Ammonium Acryloyldimethyltaurate/Vp Copolymer, Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate, Behenyl Alcohol, Arachidyl Glucoside, Acrylates/C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, Ethylhexylglycerin, Hydroxyethyl Acrylate/Sodium Acryloyldimethyl Taurate Copolymer, Potassium Sorbate, Lavandula Stoechas Extract, Sodium Phytate, C15-23 Alkane, C13-14 Alkane, Polyurethane-11, Sodium Hydroxide, Decyl Glucoside, Glycerin, Citric Acid, Tocopherol, Passiflora Edulis Fruit Extract, Manganese Violet (CI 77742).Clear Base Ingredients: Aqua/Water/Eau, Glycerin, Butylene Glycol, Carbomer, Acer Saccharum (Sugar Maple) Extract, Phenoxyethanol, Sodium Hydroxide, Polysorbate 20, Caprylyl Glycol, Disodium Edta, Glyceryl Acrylate/Acrylic Acid Copolymer, Lactobacillus Ferment, Hexylene Glycol.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: For the ultimate smooth and hydrated effect, use fingers to press primer into the skin - a little goes a long way. Start at the center of the face and work your way out.

reviews.headline: Lightweight, moisturizing with a strong lasting finish
reviews.comments:
I received this product in exchange for my honest review.

The Fenty Beauty Grip Trip Hydrating + Plumping Primer has quickly become a favorite in my routine. The formula itself is lightweight and gel-like, with skin-loving ingredients like glycerin, prickly pear cactus extract, and sodium hyaluronate that keep my skin hydrated and plump while helping makeup grip all day. It has just the faintest clean scent that disappears almost immediately, so it doesn't interfere with other products or feel overwhelming.

I also really like the packaging it comes in a sleek, clear pump bottle that feels sturdy and easy to use, and the pump dispenses just the right amount without wasting product. The product inside is visually unique. It's travel-friendly but still looks luxe sitting on my vanity.

On my skin, it gives a smooth, bouncy finish, makes foundation last longer, and doesn't cling to dry patches. The only thing to watch out for is applying too much, since it can feel a little tacky before setting.

faceoff_positive.comments:
The packaging and product are beautiful, innovative, and vibrant. When I opened the box, I couldn't help but smile at the fun, unique purple swirls. This is the innovative whimsy I've been missing in the makeup world. I only needed a little more than a pea sized amount to cover my entire face comfortably. It is unscented, which is good for sensitive skin girlies, but personally, I like a very small amount of scent to cover up the smell of the ingredients. It went on like a luxurious, hydrating moisturizer and magically dried down to a primer with just the right amount of grip to it. 

My skin looked plump, hydrated, smooth, and brighter, just minutes after application. I could have walked out of the house without adding my makeup and felt pretty. This is what skincare meets makeup is supposed to be. I was very worried it would be too grippy, but it had just the right amount without tackiness or white residue. My foundation looked better than normal, though I had to use a little more because of the firm grip texture of the primer, but it came out looking really beautiful. 

Grip Trip makes a claim that it is a "gripping primer with hydrating and visible plumping skincare benefits that delivers a smooth, hydrated finish that makes your makeup last up to 12 hours." So, I put it to a full 12 hour wear test. My makeup has never come close to staying on and looking good that long, let alone while also keeping me smoothed, plumped, and hydrated. To my absolute happy surprise, it held its claim, and I did before and after photos for it to compare, and they are nearly identical, except I'm sleepy in the 12 hour photo. I didn't expect to find a primer so useful and multifaceted, but Grip Trip is the must-have beauty product of the year. Highly recommend! I received this product in exchange for my honest review
faceoff_positive.headline: The must-have beauty product of the year!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received  this Fenty Beauty Grip Trip Hydrating and Plumping Primer for free in exchange for my honest review.

Packaging‚ÄîThe primer came in a 1 fluid ounce plastic bottle containing a clear serum with a purple primer swirl. The pump was easy to control the amount coming out. 

Scent‚ÄîThe primer has a faint clean scent that does not bother nor linger long. 

Application and Finish‚ÄîI applied all of my vitamin C, hyaluronic acid, Snail musin, moisturizer, and sun screen and then waited 10 minutes to apply the primer. It did not pill, which is a plus. It is a very smooth application , but it has more a matte finish than I would expected. 

Make up finish‚ÄîHere is where it was just fine. I tried with power foundation and then tinted moisturizer. I did not feel that it really made much of a difference. It did not really blur pores or make my make up look significantly better. However, it did not break me out, which was a plus. 

Overall, Fenty Grip Trip Hydrating and Plumping Primer is a nice product, but I did not personally feel that it was extraordinarily plumping or hydrating‚Äîat least for me.
faceoff_negative.headline: It's fine, but not life changing.
